is an overwhelming majority for this in the House of Reps (over 50% of the
congressmen are co-sponsors). I think that, at least in the case of good
people like Tom Lantos, there is a line in the sand that you cannot cross.
After all, if today we need to ignore the  Armenian genocide for politics,
tomorrow it may well be good politics to ignore the shoah or agree with
shoah deniers because of politics.

Just as an example, there was a time when Israel had this kind of motion,
which was quickly quashed, because the Turks were helping Israel with
matters pertaining to the Jews of Syria. So which is more important, helping
Jews today or ascertaining historical truths for posterity? I tend to go
with the truth, but I can see the immense problem.

